				\begin{document}$${\rm{D}}=k{\rm{\lambda }}/{\rm{\beta }}\,\mathrm{Cos}\,{\rm{\theta }}$$\end{document}where, D is average crystallite size, k is shape factor, β is full width at half maximum of each diffraction peak and θ represents the diffraction angle. In addition to hexagonal CoS phase, the peak appeared at 75.1° vouch for the existence of additional cubic phase (JCPDS No: 73–1703) of cobalt sulfide (Co3S4). Presence of cubic Co3S4 phase instigate the lattice strain and a defect in the prepared CoS sample28. To measure the induced lattice strain, Williamson-Hall plot (Fig. S2 of Supplementary Information) was derived, where 4sinθ is plotted against βcosθ. The estimated lattice strain is found to be 0.00439 and the calculated crystallite size after the correction of strain induced broadening is 67 nm (from W-H plot).Figure 2
XRD pattern of prepared CoS.

